==Old English==

===Etymology===
Common Germanic: cognates include Old Saxon [[quellian]] (Dutch [[kwellen]]), Old High German [[quellen]] (German [[quälen]]), Old Norse [[kvelja]].

===Verb===
'''cwellan''' (class 1 weak: cwelþ ‘he kills’; cwealde ‘he quelled’; ġecweald, past participle)
# to [[kill]]

